properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 4 at 1:00PM PST until January 7 at 12:00PM PST by NWS San Diego CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northeast winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to 55 mph
expected.

* WHERE...San Diego County Valleys.

* WHEN...From midnight Sunday night to noon PST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Difficult driving conditions for high profile vehicles
on I-8 through the mountains, on Highway 78 from Ramona to
Julian, and on Highway 94 from Jamul to Campo. Gusty winds could
blow around unsecured objects.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT SUNDAY NIGHT TO NOON PST TUESDAY
